                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d697">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-15T09:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 15, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Much worse tension during early evening hours yesterday. At midnight, naval
                    forces broadcast Franco’s resignation and that armed forces are in charge of the
                    Government. Calm prevails.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
